{"id":13863,"date":"2023-07-11T16:36:20","date_gmt":"2023-07-11T14:36:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/?p=13863"},"modified":"2023-07-11T16:36:20","modified_gmt":"2023-07-11T14:36:20","slug":"national-council-swear-in-new-members","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-swear-in-new-members\/","title":{"rendered":"National Council Swear-in New Members"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Windhoek \u2013 Landless People\u2019s Movement Constituency Councillors from the \/\/Kharas region were sworn-in as Members of Parliament in the National Council this morning, 11 July 2023. The MPs are returning Karasburg East Councillor, Hon. Anseline Vincentina Beukes and newly-elected Keetmanshoop Rural Constituency Councillor, Hon. Willem Labuschagne.<\/p>\n<p>The LPM seats in the National Council became vacant after Hon. Beukes and former Keetmanshoop Rural Constituency Councillor Gerrit Witbooi were elected as members of the \/\/Kharas Regional Council\u2019s Management Committee on 9 April 2021. In terms of Section 18[4] of the Regional Councils Act, \u201cA member of a regional council, who is elected as a member of the management committee of the regional council, under this section is not eligible for election as a member of the National Council under section 26.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>The MPs were sworn in at the start of the session by His Lordship, Chief Justice Peter Shivute. After the House adjourned, they paid a visit to the Secretary, Advocate Tousy Namiseb and thereafter, held a briefing with the Chairperson, Hon. Lukas Muha.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Windhoek \u2013 Landless People\u2019s Movement Constituency Councillors from the \/\/Kharas region were sworn-in as Members of Parliament in the National Council this morning, 11 July 2023. The MPs are returning Karasburg East Councillor, Hon. Anseline Vincentina Beukes and newly-elected Keetmanshoop Rural Constituency Councillor, Hon. Willem Labuschagne. The LPM seats in the National Council became vacant&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":8,"featured_media":13864,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[159,39],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-13863","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-home-page-slider","category-news","category-159","category-39","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13863","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/8"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=13863"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13863\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":13865,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13863\/revisions\/13865"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/13864"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=13863"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=13863"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=13863"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}